ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) — Facundo Torres scored a penalty-kick goal and Pedro Gallese made five saves to lead Orlando City to a 1-0 victory over the New York Red Bulls in a season opener on Saturday.Torres’ game-winner came in the 56th minute after a foul on the Red Bulls’ Sean Nealis.New York outshot Orlando City 15-2 with a 5-1 edge in shots on goal.Orlando City beat the Red Bulls for a third straight time to improve to 6-9-2 in head-to-head matches.New York tied a MLS record with five straight road wins to open the season last year.Both teams next play Saturday, with Orlando hosting Cincinnati, while the Red Bulls host Nashville.___The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.